name: Room in Deco Apartment, Brunswick East
description: A large air conditioned room with firm queen spring mattress bed in a vintage apartment. Located right outside is a tram to the city just 20 minutes away. This area is known for its arts culture, live music, cafes and international food.
neighborhood_overview:
This hip area is a crossroads between two great cultural strips of inner Northern Melbourne.
Located in East Brunswick, between High St, Northcote and Lygon St Brunswick you have the choice of some of Melbourne's best budget dining and cool bars. Restaurants range from cheap eateries to quality Lebanese and Turkish with Indian, Greek, Italian and Thai places. Around the corner Ceres Environmental Centre is set on reclaimed parkland next to Merri creek and it's convenient bike paths. Ceres has a daily organic foods market and two cafes with outdoor and indoor dining. They also have a bike shed where you can buy a second hand bike cheap - or take your own to work on. There are three coffee places within 50metres, and the Lomond Hotel Pub right across the road has good live music.
host_about: As an artist working in animation and video I am involved in many community related projects. I manage a Yoga studio at this address, downstairs from the flat. I really enjoy Yoga, good food, good company and getting out into the sunshine whenever I can. Melbourne is a great city of arts and music - there's always something on and my flat is in a great location between Brunswick and Northcote, two suburbs with many arts warehouses and venues. Please be aware that the apartment is old and has a funky vibe and it is not for people who need  modern hotel style accommodation.

description:
The absolute centre of Melbourne, this open-plan warehouse is full of natural light and loads of character. Easy walking distance to all points in the city as well as Southbank, Docklands, Carlton and Fitzroy. One of a kind laneway experience and Rankins Lane is one of the most interesting laneways with pop-ups and hidden businesses in the upper levels.

Parties, events and gatherings of any kind are not permitted.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the centre of Melbourne, not just the CBD but the actual middle of everything. Plus, it is in a laneway, one of Melbourne's most beloved features, with two excellent cafes, one at each end, Brother Baba Budan and Manchester Press. Around the corner in Somerset Place, I recommend Captains of Industry, a semi-hidden upstairs cafe that's an oasis when the city is busy. The clock also includes Paris Cat jazz bar, Picolina premium ice cream shop, Miznon, the popular Israeli pita restaurant, Myrtle bar, Whitehart bar, Tipo 00 and Osteria Ilaria, two fantastic Italian restaurants. For incredible local gifts and souvenirs, visit Wilkins and Kent.

Rankins Lane is a small lane located in the central business district of Melbourne, Victoria, Australia. It is located between Bourke and Little Collins streets. The lane is known for its street art and trendy cafes.

neighborhood_overview: Altona is a quiet seaside village with a beach that gets very busy if the weather is very, very hot. It is also favorite place for kite boarding and the sight of many colourful kites flying in the air as the boarders skim over the sea surface is beautiful. As well Williamstown, the first port in Melbourne with many colonial and Victorian buildings is just 10 minutes drive away. It is a mecca for fine dining, snazzy shopping and great restaurants as well as many fine yacht clubs.

name: Sunny 1950s Apartment, St Kilda East  Longer stays
description: Greyfriars is an iconic apartment block with a beautiful central garden, a car park and our sunny 1950s renovated one bedroom flat. Green views from living and bedroom, a cute separate kitchen and a retro bathroom.  Walk to shops, tram to city. Your pied-a-terre in vibrant Melbourne.
neighborhood_overview:
Greyfriars is an iconic 1950s apartment block built near the top of East St Kilda hill. Stately mansions like Labassa and Grimwade House are a stones throw away. The area is green and residential but a walk, a tram or a short drive away, and you are in all the action of Balaclava, Ripponlea and Elsternwick.

Stroll down Orrong Road to Glover Station, an eatery in Glen Eira Road or to Ripponlea Village to visit the Firebrand Bakery or for a fabulous brunch. Walk down the Balaclava Road hill to eclectic Balaclava with its cafes, restaurants, bars, bakeries and shops. And tram back up the hill if you are feeling lazy.

The St Kilda Esplanade, Luna Park and Ackland Street are a short tram ride away on the no 16 or 3A trams. Enjoy the tram a little longer and you are in Melbourne's CBD on either the no 16, 3 or 3A. (The no 3 takes you to the City via a different route to Ackland Street and St Kilda Beach)

Alternatively you can take the train from Balaclav
host_about:
We live on a broad acre cropping, sheep and alpaca farm on the Wimmera plains, enjoying the space, people, environment and the ability to grow our own produce. 

Our beach house on the Great Ocean Road and our city apartment are a wonderful contrast to life on the farm. _x000D_
_x000D_
Satis Beach House is comfortable, quirky and just around the corner from a beautiful surf beach, estuary and cliff top walks along the coastline of south eastern Australia.  Excellent cafes, restaurants, a bookshop, galleries, surf club and pub add to the coastal mix at Aireys Inlet._x000D_
_x000D_
Greyfriars is an iconic mid century apartment block with a lovely central garden in St Kilda East, Melbourne.  This sweet one bedroom apartment is our city AC/a!Epied AA  terreAC/a!aC/ and we love it.

name: Huge bright townhouse with terrace
neighborhood_overview: Seddon is a great place and growing by the minute but is still quiet and retains its village like atmosphere. There's great cafes and fantastic coffee,a gourmet supermarket,wine shop and a variety of restaurants from African (my favourite!) to Malaysian and Italian,and all within walking distance to the property. Just down the road is Footscray,a predominately Vietnamese community with a bit of African too,so wonderful food choices everywhere,including the Footscray Market with its fresh fruit and veg,meat and seafood. Seddon also has an eclectic mix of shops ranging from gifts shops like Sedonia to vintage shops like my very own "Once More With Feeling" at the front of the property on Charles St. So you must drop in and say hi when you stay! Its a great friendly neighbourhood that you will fall in love with and not far from the city either or major attractions like Flemington Racecourse and Etihad stadium. Leave your car and take public transport or an Uber, it's that easy.
host_about: hi my name is jo and I run my own small business, a Vintage clothing boutique called Once More,with Feeling. The shop is actually at the front of the AirBnb so drop in and say hi when you come to stay. I'm also involved in Theatre and have performed many times at a wonderful Melbourne institution called La Mama. I love music and feel so lucky to live in Melbourne where we have a great live music scene. Sometimes i sing and play guitar and I love both country and western music,I also sing in the Melbourne Mass Gospel choir. My partner is Ray,who is a builder and is responsible for the wonderful renovation at Seddon and who sometimes builds sets for the theatre too. We love to travel and after using airbnb will probably never stay at a hotel again we love it so much. we hope you love it too and will love visiting the west of Melbourne, a wonderfully multicultural place so close to the city and with everything you could imagine.
